# type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:10
msgid "Service and Host Freshness Checks"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:13
msgid ""
"Nagios supports a feature that does <quote>freshness</quote> checking on the "
"results of host and service checks. The purpose of freshness checking is to "
"ensure that host and service checks are being provided passively by external "
"applications on a regular basis."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:16
msgid ""
"Freshness checking is useful when you want to ensure that <link linkend="
"\"thebasics-passivechecks\">passive checks</link> are being received as "
"frequently as you want. This can be very useful in <link linkend="
"\"advancedtopics-distributed\">distributed</link> and <link linkend="
"\"advancedtopics-redundancy\">failover</link> monitoring environments."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:23
msgid "How Does Freshness Checking Work?"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:25
msgid ""
"<inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"images/freshness.png"
"\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> Nagios periodically "
"checks the freshness of the results for all hosts services that have "
"freshness checking enabled."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:34
msgid "A freshness threshold is calculated for each host or service."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:37
msgid ""
"For each host/service, the age of its last check result is compared with the "
"freshness threshold."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:41
msgid ""
"If the age of the last check result is greater than the freshness threshold, "
"the check result is considered <quote>stale</quote>."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:45
msgid ""
"If the check results is found to be stale, Nagios will force an <link "
"linkend=\"thebasics-activechecks\">active check</link> of the host or "
"service by executing the command specified by in the host or service "
"definition."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><tip><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:50
msgid ""
"An active check is executed even if active checks are disabled on a program-"
"wide or host- or service-specific basis."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:52
msgid ""
"For example, if you have a freshness threshold of 60 for one of your "
"services, Nagios will consider that service to be stale if its last check "
"result is older than 60 seconds."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:56
msgid "Enabling Freshness Checking"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:57
msgid "Here's what you need to do to enable freshness checking..."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:60
msgid ""
"Enable freshness checking on a program-wide basis with the <link linkend="
"\"configuringnagios-configmain-check_service_freshness"
"\">check_service_freshness</link> and <link linkend=\"configuringnagios-"
"configmain-check_host_freshness\">check_host_freshness</link> directives."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:65
msgid ""
"Use <link linkend=\"configuringnagios-configmain-"
"service_freshness_check_interval\">service_freshness_check_interval</link> "
"and <link linkend=\"configuringnagios-configmain-"
"host_freshness_check_interval\">host_freshness_check_interval</link> options "
"to tell Nagios how often in should check the freshness of service and host "
"results."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:70
msgid ""
"Enable freshness checking on a host- and service-specific basis by setting "
"the <varname>check_freshness</varname> option in your host and service "
"definitions to a value of 1."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:75
msgid ""
"Configure freshness thresholds by setting the <varname>freshness_threshold</"
"varname> option in your host and service definitions."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:79
msgid ""
"Configure the <varname>check_command</varname> option in your host or "
"service definitions to reflect a valid command that should be used to "
"actively check the host or service when it is detected as stale."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:84
msgid ""
"The <varname>check_period</varname> option in your host and service "
"definitions is used when Nagios determines when a host or service can be "
"checked for freshness, so make sure it is set to a valid timeperiod."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><tip><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:89
msgid ""
"If you do not specify a host- or service-specific "
"<varname>freshness_threshold</varname> value (or you set it to zero), Nagios "
"will automatically calculate a threshold automatically, based on a how often "
"you monitor that particular host or service. I would recommended that you "
"explicitly specify a freshness threshold, rather than let Nagios pick one "
"for you."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:96
msgid ""
"An example of a service that might require freshness checking might be one "
"that reports the status of your nightly backup jobs. Perhaps you have a "
"external script that submit the results of the backup job to Nagios once the "
"backup is completed.  In this case, all of the checks/results for the "
"service are provided by an external application using passive checks. In "
"order to ensure that the status of the backup job gets reported every day, "
"you may want to enable freshness checking for the service.  If the external "
"script doesn't submit the results of the backup job, you can have Nagios "
"fake a critical result by doing something like this..."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:104
msgid ""
"Here's what the definition for the service might look like (some required "
"options are omitted)..."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><programlisting>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"define service{\n"
"\t\t        host_name               backup-server\n"
"\t\t        service_description     ArcServe Backup Job\n"
"\t\t        active_checks_enabled   0               ; active checks are NOT enabled\n"
"\t\t        passive_checks_enabled  1               ; passive checks are enabled (this is how results are reported)\n"
"\t\t        check_freshness         1\n"
"\t\t        freshness_threshold     93600           ; 26 hour threshold, since backups may not always finish at the same time\n"
"\t\t        check_command           no-backup-report        ; this command is run only if the service results are <quote>stale</quote>\n"
"\t\t        ...other options...\n"
"\t\t        }"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:116
msgid ""
"Notice that active checks are disabled for the service. This is because the "
"results for the service are only made by an external application using "
"passive checks.  Freshness checking is enabled and the freshness threshold "
"has been set to 26 hours.  This is a bit longer than 24 hours because backup "
"jobs sometimes run late from day to day (depending on how much data there is "
"to backup, how much network traffic is present, etc.). The"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:121
msgid ""
"command is executed only if the results of the service are determined to be "
"stale. The definition of the"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:122
msgid "command might look like this..."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><programlisting>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"define command{\n"
"\t\t        command_name    no-backup-report\n"
"\t\t        command_line    /usr/local/nagios/libexec/check_dummy 2 \"CRITICAL: Results of backup job were not reported!\"\n"
"\t\t        }"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:128
msgid "If Nagios detects that the service results are stale, it will run the"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: AdvancedTopics/freshness.xml:129
msgid ""
"command as an active service check. This causes the &plugin-dummy; plugin to "
"be executed, which returns a critical state to Nagios. The service will then "
"go into to a critical state (if it isn't already there) and someone will "
"probably get notified of the problem."
msgstr ""
